                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>This inscription, dated in the <hi rend="bold">8th year,</hi> states that the maṇḍapa [in front of the central shrine in the Vaikuṇṭha-Perumāḷ temple in the village] was constructed by <hi rend="bold">Araśāḻvār,</hi> the elder sister of <hi rend="bold">Āḷappiṟandār Aḻagiyaśīyar</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Peṟugai,</hi> who was probably a member of a collateral branch of the Peruñjiṅga family with headquarters at Peṟugai.</p>						
                            
                            <p>The village Peṟugai cannot be satisfactorily identified, but it is probably to be located in Peṟugaṉūr-nāḍu in Tirumuṉaippāḍi.<note><hi rend="italic">A.R.</hi> No. 45 of 1903.</note> Peṟugaṉūr is probably the same as Periyaṉūr in the Tirukkoyilur taluk.<note>[Peṟugai may be Peṟuganūr itself - Ed.]</note></p>						
                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
